HEADWORD: madake
<hw>madake</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>large bamboo having thick-walled
culms; native of China and perhaps Japan; widely brown
elsewhere.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> giant timber bamboo, ku-chiku, Phyllostachys
bambusoides.</syn>⟦br⟧
